      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at our quarterly reports and shrinkage is up like 5% compared to last period. how do i factor that into our inventory turnover ratio? i need to show the impact on the overall efficiency of the warehouse.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Shrinkage, an increase of 5% in your quarterly reports, means you've lost some inventory, which will directly impact your inventory turnover ratio. Think of shrinkage as a hidden inventory loss, as the average inventory you're tracking is now inflated by these missing goods. You need to adjust your Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) or your ending inventory figures to reflect this loss before calculating the turnover ratio. This will show the true efficiency, or lack thereof, of your warehouse operations.",
