    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah i get that. it's just frustrating because we've checked the cameras and the logs and it's like things just vanish. it's small amounts of high-value stuff, very hard to track. any ideas on how to improve security or audit processes to stop this happening in the first place?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For small, high-value items vanishing, you need a more robust system than just basic cameras. Consider implementing a system where every item, especially those high-value pieces, gets a unique tracking tag, perhaps a small RFID tag or a serialized barcode that updates in real-time. You could also institute more frequent, random spot audits, not just full inventory counts. These proactive measures will make it harder for any low-level theft to go unnoticed.",
      "source": "target",
